ation, and after thread termination. The documentation confirms this pattern, so I've identified two minor gaps: \"DataReader\" is missing from the s1 hints despite being referenced in the content, and both \"DataReader\" and \"NoMoreRecord\" are absent from s3 hints even though they appear as \"DataReader.NoMoreRecord\" in the actual implementation details.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":25716,"cache_read_input_tokens":29873,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":25716,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e3292cef-60fa-4b94-8900-5a4e78aa4baf","uuid":"02218c95-388f-4265-aaf8-61edf4d459fa"}
